Get parameters

get_param-ConsensusPartition-method.Rd

Get parameters

# S4 method for ConsensusPartition
get_param(object, k = object@k, unique = TRUE)

Arguments

object

A ConsensusPartition-class object.
k

Number of partitions.
unique

Whether apply unique to rows of the returned data frame.

Details

It is mainly used internally.

Value

A data frame of parameters corresponding to the current k. In the data frame, each row corresponds to a partition run.

Examples

data(cola_rl)
obj = cola_rl["sd", "kmeans"]
get_param(obj)
#>    top_n k n_row n_col
#> 1     20 2    16    60
#> 2     30 2    24    60
#> 3     40 2    32    60
#> 4     20 3    16    60
#> 5     30 3    24    60
#> 6     40 3    32    60
#> 7     20 4    16    60
#> 8     30 4    24    60
#> 9     40 4    32    60
#> 10    20 5    16    60
#> 11    30 5    24    60
#> 12    40 5    32    60
#> 13    20 6    16    60
#> 14    30 6    24    60
#> 15    40 6    32    60
get_param(obj, k = 2)
#>   top_n k n_row n_col
#> 1    20 2    16    60
#> 2    30 2    24    60
#> 3    40 2    32    60
get_param(obj, unique = FALSE)
